{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "55e7a3b0-1f2c-4d8e-9b6a-7c3d2e1f0a9b",
    "name": "Untung Utuh API",
    "description": "## Untung Utuh — Complete API Test Collection\n\n### Quick Start\n1. Import this file **and** `Untung Utuh — Dev.postman_environment.json`\n2. Select the **Untung Utuh — Dev** environment in the top-right dropdown\n3. Open **Collection Runner** (▶ Run Collection) and run folders in this order:\n   `Auth` → `Stores` → `Products` → `Upload` → `Analytics` → `Validation Errors`\n4. Every test auto-propagates `authToken`, `storeId`, and `productId` to the environment\n\n### Prerequisites\n- Backend running locally on `http://localhost:5001`\n- MongoDB accessible (local Docker or Atlas)\n- **Cloudinary** credentials in backend `.env` (required for Upload tests)\n- Run against **dev/staging only** — never production\n\n### Cleanup\nTest accounts use the `test_` prefix (`test_user@example.com`). Delete them after testing or use a dedicated test DB.\n\n### Note on Store\nThere is no `POST /stores` endpoint yet. After the **Auth** folder runs, manually paste your `storeId` into the environment (or check DB / run `GET /stores/my` from the Stores folder to auto-extract it).",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      { "key": "token", "value": "{{authToken}}", "type": "string" }
    ]
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl",   "value": "http://localhost:5001/api", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "authToken", "value": "",                          "type": "string" },
    { "key": "storeId",   "value": "",                          "type": "string" },
    { "key": "productId", "value": "",                          "type": "string" }
  ],
  "item": [

    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "item": [

        {
          "name": "Register (test user)",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"test_seller\",\n  \"email\": \"test_user@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"Password123!\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/register",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "register"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "// Register returns 201 on success, 409 if email already exists — both are acceptable",
                  "pm.test('Status is 201 or 409', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([201, 409]);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.test('Response status is success', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(json.status).to.eql('success');",
                  "  });",
                  "  pm.test('Token is a string', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(json.token).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
                  "  });",
                  "  pm.test('User has _id and email', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(json.data.user._id).to.be.a('string');",
                  "    pm.expect(json.data.user.email).to.eql('test_user@example.com');",
                  "  });",
                  "  pm.environment.set('authToken', json.token);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },

        {
          "name": "Login",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"test_user@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"Password123!\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/login",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "login"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response status is success', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(json.status).to.eql('success');",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Token is a non-empty string', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(json.token).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('User object contains email', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(json.data.user.email).to.eql('test_user@example.com');",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Password is not exposed', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(json.data.user.password).to.be.undefined;",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "// Propagate token for all subsequent requests",
                  "pm.environment.set('authToken', json.token);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },

        {
          "name": "Get Me",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/me",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "me"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response status is success', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(json.status).to.eql('success');",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('User matches logged-in account', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(json.data.user.email).to.eql('test_user@example.com');",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Password is not exposed', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(json.data.user.password).to.be.undefined;",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },

